## 🔍 Sensitivity Analysis – Key Scenarios

| Scenario                                           | Adjustments                                          | Revenue Δ    | EBITDA Δ | 5‑yr FCF Δ                 | Estimated Equity IRR |
| -------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | ------------ | -------- | -------------------------- | -------------------- |
| **Base Case**                                      | —                                                    | —            | —        | —                          | **\~19 %**           |
| **A. Pricing Up +10 %**                            | Real‑estate prices +10 %; ADR +8 %; Marina fees +5 % | +95 M        | +33 M    | +27 M                      | **\~22 %**           |
| **B. Pricing Down ‑10 %**                          | Real‑estate prices ‑10 %; ADR ‑8 %                   | ‑95 M        | ‑33 M    | ‑27 M                      | **\~16 %**           |
| **C. Interest Rate +200 bps**                      | Debt coupon 8 % fixed                                | —            | (—)      | ‑22 M (extra debt service) | **\~17 %**           |
| **D. Slower Absorption (‑20 % villas sold by Y2)** | Push 20 % villa sales into Y3‑4; holding costs +5 M  | Timing shift | –        | ‑18 M                      | **\~15 %**           |
| **E. Combined Downside (B + C + D)**               | Pricing ‑10 %, rate +200 bps, slow sales             | ‑95 M        | ‑33 M    | ‑67 M                      | **\~13 %**           |
| **F. Upside Blend (A + faster sales)**             | Pricing +10 %, villas 10 % faster, rate unchanged    | +110 M       | +38 M    | +35 M                      | **\~24 %**           |

> *Δ figures vs. base; EBITDA & FCF impacts rounded. IRR recalculated with revised cash flows & timing. Detailed model available on request.*

